The main changes made to the code are:

1. In the CSS styles, the `marker` fill color is set to `black` to make the arrows visible:
```css
marker {
    fill: black;
}
```

2. In the `<defs>` section of the SVG, the `refX` attribute of the `<marker>` element is set to `8` to adjust the position of the arrow tip:
```html
<marker id="arrow" viewBox="0 -5 10 10" refX="8" refY="0" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto">
    <path d="M0,-5L10,0L0,5" fill="black"></path>
</marker>
```

3. The `fill` property of the `.link-label` class is set to `black` to ensure the link labels have a visible color:
```css
.link-label {
    font: 10px sans-serif;
    fill: black;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 0 #fff, 1px 0 0 #fff, 0 -1px 0 #fff, -1px 0 0 #fff;
}
```

With these changes, the arrows should be visible in black color, and the link labels should be visible with a black color as well.

If the text labels and arrows are still not visible after making these changes, please check the generated HTML in the browser's developer tools to see if there are any conflicting styles or elements that might be hiding them. Additionally, ensure that the `graph.links` array contains the necessary data for the link labels and that the `d.title` property is defined for each link.
